HEADWORD: Pyrocitric
<hw>Pyr`o*cit"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pyro-</ets> + <ets>citric</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pyrocitrique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to,
or designating, any one of three acids obtained by the distillation of
citric acid, and called respectively <altname>citraconic</altname>,
<altname>itaconic</altname>, and <altname>mesaconic</altname>
<it>acid.</it></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

